sec.p:
Such a gear raises two problems:


the correlation of the values of geometrical parameters rb1,rb2,e, so that the motion function ϕ2(S1) and the clearance jn between the teeth to have acceptable variation ranges;

finding practical applications, considering functionality, as well as the variation range of the transmission ratio (which is equivalent with the variation range of the radius r2r=OrCr).

The numerical simulation is performed on the basis of specific demands of the automotives’ steering boxes, the gear defined here having exactly this destination. These demands are referring to:


implementing the prescribed rotation φ2 for the cogged sector (ϕ2max<50∘), usually ϕ2max≅40∘;

implementing the variation field of the transmission ratio (Γ=r2max/r2r 0≅1.3).
